title: Conference Call to Brief Journalists on Vice President Biden's Upcoming Trip to Southeastern Europe | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




May 15, 2009

 



Conference Call to Brief Journalists on Vice President Biden's Upcoming Trip to Southeastern Europe




THE WHITE HOUSE  Office of the Vice President   __________________________________________ For Immediate Release           May 15, 2009  *MEDIA ADVISORY* Conference Call to Brief Journalists on Vice President Biden’s Upcoming Trip to Southeastern Europe  Washington, DC – A senior administration official will hold conference call on FRIDAY, May 15th at 2:15 PM EDT to brief journalists on background on the Vice President’s upcoming trip to Southeastern Europe.  During the week of May 18th, the Vice President will visit Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia and Kosovo.  During the visit, the Vice President will meet with the political leadership in all three countries, as well as U.S. officials and military personnel stationed in the region.  WHAT:         Conference Call to Brief Journalists on the Vice President’s upcoming trip to Southeastern Europe TIME:         2:15 PM EDT Dial-in:      Please email press@ovp.eop.gov for dial-in information  ###
